sentences: Woody Lee (born April 1, 1968 in Garland, Texas) is an American country music singer and songwriter.
Signed to Atlantic Records in 1995, he released his debut album Get Over It that year.
Before the release of his album, he co-wrote "I See It Now" for fellow labelmate Tracy Lawrence.
He also wrote Shenandoah's 1995 single "Always Have, Always Will".
